"Where a function call has a single argument, and that argument is formatted "
"across multiple-lines, format the outer call as if it were a single-line "
"call, if the result fits. Apply the same combining behaviour to any similar "
"expressions which have multi-line, block-indented lists of sub-expressions "
"delimited by parentheses (e.g., macros or tuple struct literals). E.g.,"
msgstr ""

#: src/expressions.md:928
msgid "Apply this behavior recursively."
